beerName: Free State Cloud Hopper Imperial IPA
reviewBlob:
Buttery smooth beer from a historic brewery. Very happy to have tried some Free State beer.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Interesting beer. I can definitely taste the barrel aging they spoke of. Boozy, but not overwhelming. Extra dry-hopping comes through, as well. Beautiful burnt-orange/copper hue. Neat beer.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Bourbon. Bourbon, bourbon, bourbon. A tad bit too much bourbon, but delicious nonetheless. Huge bourbon, chocolate, licorice aroma. Palate is a boozy plum with burnt chocolate notes. Mouth feel is strong upfront with a cooling alcohol burn that lingers and is quite pleasing. So happy to finally try this beer!

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

For such an outrageous beer, I have to give Dogfish Head credit for making this as drinkable and tasty as it is. Very happy I finally got to try it!

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Pours an opaque yellow with a white head. Sweet, boozy flavor. Bright aroma.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Nose is sweet, boozy, and a burnt-sugary goodness. Crystal clear golden-copper with a lingering head and lacing. Taste is tropical, almost pineapple-like, boozy, with just enough bitterness. I'd love to do a shoot-out next to the first Ruination, but if memory serves me correctly, this is slightly less flavorful. Still a fantastic beer.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

I wish I had the patience to let this age a bit, but I don't. It literally has an "enjoy after" date on it, oh well. Still a great beer. Aroma's fantastic - earthy, boozy, sweet. Taste's fantastic - boozy, yeasty, aged fruit, malty. I personally love the look of this beer - color of a dirty penny, oily, and earthy. It almost reminds me of Rochefort 10, a Trappist beer. 

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

This BEER tastes like cat pee and smells like cat pee. It's even better with the lights off. The cat pee is prevalent. Four out of five.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

This BEER tastes like cat pee and smells like cat pee. It's even better with the lights off. The cat pee is prevalent. Four out of five.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Currently sitting in the brewery cafe sipping fresh Hopslam on draft. Amazing. Pours a honey gold, great lacing, with a sweet, dank aroma. Taste starts off with a wave of bitter booze that melts away into that honey, hoppy goodness. Again, amazing. Kalamazoo is a cool little town, too. Great daytime roadtrip from Chicago!

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

beerName: Pipeworks Ninja vs. Unicorn Double IPA
reviewBlob:
Finally got this one and it blew me away. Bubblegum, citrus, marijuana dank goodness. That will be all.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Just paid $21 for a four pack. Totally, completely, wholly worth it. That's my review. Hope it's helpful.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Being from St. Louis and having this be one of my earliest go-to craft beers, it's tough to rate this. Aroma is citrusy with strong malt notes. Malty, grapefruit flavor with almost zero hop dank, which I love oh so much. Low ABV. Overall decent Pale Ale from a great St. Louis brewery. Go Cardinals.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

beerName: Avery The Maharaja Imperial India Pale Ale
reviewBlob:
Surprise attacked it's way into my top five favorite beers. So good. Really caught me off guard.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

My god. I've had Dreadnaught a few times from a bomber (which is awesome in it's own right), but experiencing it fresh at the Brewery on tap is a completely different, and amazing experience. The perfect Imperial IPA. 

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Three Floyds Imperials just don't surprise me anymore. Tap at the three Floyds Brewpub. Drank immediately after a Dreadnaught on tap, which probably wasn't a good idea (the fresh, draft Dreadnaught was unbelievable), but it still held its own. Incredibly floral for its ABV, and really tasty. Must try.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

beerName: Half Acre Galactic Double Daisy Cutter
reviewBlob:
Taste is cat pee and the aroma cat pee. This beer is gay. Better in the daylight.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Really excited about this one, being from Chicago. Beautiful color, moderate lacing. Aroma is fantastic. Fruity and resiny. Taste is a balanced, hop powered yet fruity wave of deliciousness. Four pack for $9.99. Great value for a great beer. Try if you can.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

On tap. Couldn't believe this was at just under a 3.5 rating. Awesome aroma, great hoppy flavor, and poured a beautiful, clear, deep copper. One of the best pale ales I've had.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

This beer is SMELLY and GAY. What the FUCK? What the FUCK? What the FUCK? This beer is SMELLY and GAY?

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

I'm waiting for the overall rating of this beer to steadily rise as more folks try it because this is an EXCELLENT Imperial IPA. I've always really enjoyed Sixpoint's Resin, but this upgraded, hop-tacular version knocked it out of the park for me. Beautiful appearance and strong, resiny, hoppy goodness in the flavor. High ABV provides an outstanding warmth to accompany the huge taste. 

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Great offering by SN. Aromas not as strong as I had hoped, but I was pleasantly surprised by the taste. Worth the try.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Not my type of beer, but the hype encouraged me to try. Pleasantly satisfied. Plums, grapefruit, honey, sourdough, and booze. Delicious. A little too carbonated for my taste. This might force me to try more of the Belgian styled ale.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Not a bad beer by any means. A little light for me. Taste is floral and hoppy but short lived with little to no aftertaste. Hardly any aroma. Happy to try a Wisconsin beer during our visit to the state. When in Rome, as they say.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Tasted like an old Budweiser. Appearance isn't bad. Pours a deep, crisp, clear, caramel amber. Again, however, the taste is horrific.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

The quintessential IPA. Great aroma, balanced yet hoppy flavor, and, in my opinion, a perfect ABV for and IPA (7%). Perfect go-to beer due to its wide availability. One of my favorites!

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone
